<h1>Privacy Policy for Marble Blaster</h1>

<p><strong>Last updated:</strong> November 19, 2025</p>

<h2>1. Introduction</h2>
<p>
Marble Blaster is a puzzle and action game designed for users ages 6 and up, including teens and adults. 
We respect the privacy of all players and are committed to providing a safe and secure gaming experience. 
This privacy policy explains what information the app uses and how it is handled. We comply with the 
Google Play Developer Program Policies, the Families Policy Requirements, and Google Play’s 
<strong>Data Safety</strong> rules.
</p>

<h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
<p>
Marble Blaster includes an optional <strong>online leaderboard</strong> that allows players to compare 
scores with others. To support this feature, the game collects only the minimal information required 
for leaderboard functionality.
</p>

<p>The app collects the following data:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Anonymous Player ID</strong> – A randomly generated identifier that cannot be used 
      to identify the user personally.</li>
  <li><strong>Leaderboard Scores</strong> – High scores, rankings, and achievement data.</li>
  <li><strong>Gameplay Data</strong> – Basic progress data such as levels completed or best times.</li>
</ul>

<p>
This information is stored securely in the cloud to enable leaderboard updates and synchronization.
It is linked only to the anonymous player ID.
</p>

<p>
<strong>No personal information is collected.</strong><br>
We do <strong>not</strong> collect names, emails, phone numbers, photos, real-world location, device 
identifiers, or any sensitive data from users of any age.
</p>

<h2>3. How Information Is Used</h2>
<p>The collected data is used solely for:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Displaying your score and rank on the game leaderboard</li>
  <li>Saving gameplay progress</li>
  <li>Synchronizing progress across devices (if supported)</li>
</ul>

<p>
The data is never used for advertising, tracking, analytics, or profiling.
</p>

<h2>4. Information We Do NOT Collect</h2>
<p>Marble Blaster does <strong>not</strong> collect or request:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Names or contact information</li>
  <li>Email addresses</li>
  <li>Precise or approximate location data</li>
  <li>Device identifiers (Android ID, IP address, advertising ID)</li>
  <li>Photos, videos, microphone access, or any media</li>
  <li>Contacts, messages, or files</li>
  <li>Biometric or health information</li>
  <li>Analytics or usage tracking</li>
  <li>Personal information from children, teens, or adults</li>
</ul>

<h2>5. Third-Party Services</h2>
<p>
Marble Blaster does <strong>not</strong> include ads, analytics SDKs, social media logins, or 
tracking technologies. No personal data is shared with third parties.
</p>

<p>
If cloud services or servers are used to maintain leaderboard functions, they are used solely to 
store anonymous IDs and score data. No personal data is ever transferred.
</p>

<h2>6. Users Ages 6 and Older</h2>
<p>
Marble Blaster is suitable for players ages 6 and above. The game is designed to ensure safety 
for younger players while remaining enjoyable for teens and adults. Since the app does not 
collect personal information, it is appropriate and safe for children under the Families Policy 
requirements.
</p>

<p>
Leaderboard entries use <strong>anonymous IDs only</strong> to ensure the privacy of users of all ages.
</p>

<h2>7. Permissions</h2>
<p>
Marble Blaster may request the following permissions:
</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>INTERNET</strong> – Required to submit and retrieve leaderboard information.</li>
  <li><strong>ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE</strong> – Used to check whether an internet connection is available.</li>
</ul>

<p>No other permissions are requested.</p>

<h2>8. Internet Use</h2>
<p>
The game can be played offline. Internet access is required only for:
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Submitting leaderboard scores</li>
  <li>Displaying leaderboard rankings</li>
  <li>Optional cloud progress sync</li>
</ul>

<h2>9. Data Security</h2>
<p>
All stored data is protected with industry-standard security measures. Only anonymous player IDs 
and game-related data (not personal information) are stored. This information cannot be linked to 
a real-world identity.
</p>

<h2>10. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
<p>
If we modify this Privacy Policy, the “Last Updated” date will be changed. Updates will remain 
available for review.
</p>

<h2>11. Contact Us</h2>
<p>
If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us:<br>
<strong>Email:</strong> issa.christopher@protonmail.com
</p>

</body>
